<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKragh1989">Kragh, Helge (1989), <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=d2zy_QSq2b0C&amp;pg=PA121&amp;lpg=PA121&amp;dq=%22secondary+source%22+historiography&amp;source=web&amp;ots=9v7A99Rzbf&amp;sig=jNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=d2zy_QSq2b0C&amp;pg=PA121&amp;lpg=PA121&amp;dq=%22secondary+source%22+historiography&amp;source=web&amp;ots=9v7A99Rzbf&amp;sig=jNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4" rel="nofollow">An Introduction to the Historiography of Science</a></i>, Cambridge University Press, p.&#160;121, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0521389216" class="internal">ISBN 0521389216</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=d2zy_QSq2b0C&amp;pg=PA121&amp;lpg=PA121&amp;dq=%22secondary+source%22+historiography&amp;source=web&amp;ots=9v7A99Rzbf&amp;sig=jNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=d2zy_QSq2b0C&amp;pg=PA121&amp;lpg=PA121&amp;dq=%22secondary+source%22+historiography&amp;source=web&amp;ots=9v7A99Rzbf&amp;sig=jNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=d2zy_QSq2b0C&amp;pg=PA121&amp;lpg=PA121&amp;dq=%22secondary+source%22+historiography&amp;source=web&amp;ots=9v7A99Rzbf&amp;sig=jNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=An+Introduction+to+the+Historiography+of+Science&amp;rft.aulast=Kragh&amp;rft.aufirst=Helge&amp;rft.au=Kragh%2C+Helge&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B121&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0521389216&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dd2zy_QSq2b0C%26pg%3DPA121%26lpg%3DPA121%26dq%3D%2522secondary%2Bsource%2522%2Bhistoriography%26source%3Dweb%26ots%3D9v7A99Rzbf%26sig%3DjNrIeEdaovpKIuX_jD9KlrGO2-4&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Primary_source"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> ("[T]he distinction is not a sharp one. Since a source is only a source in a specific historical context, the same source object can be both a primary or secondary source according to what it is used for."); <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDelgadilloLynch1999">Delgadillo, Roberto; Lynch, Beverly (1999), "<a href="http://www.ala.org/ala/acrl/acrlpubs/crljournal/backissues1999b/may99/delgadillo.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ala.org/ala/acrl/acrlpubs/crljournal/backissues1999b/may99/delgadillo.pdf" rel="nofollow">Future Historians: Their Quest for Information</a>" (PDF), <i>College &amp; Research Libraries</i>: 245–259, at 253<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.ala.org/ala/acrl/acrlpubs/crljournal/backissues1999b/may99/delgadillo.pdf" class="external free" title="http://www.ala.org/ala/acrl/acrlpubs/crljournal/backissues1999b/may99/delgadillo.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://www.ala.org/ala/acrl/acrlpubs/crljournal/backissues1999b/may99/delgadillo.pdf</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Future+Historians%3A+Their+Quest+for+Information&amp;rft.jtitle=College+%26+Research+Libraries&amp;rft.aulast=Delgadillo&amp;rft.aufirst=Roberto&amp;rft.au=Delgadillo%2C+Roberto&amp;rft.au=Lynch%2C+Beverly&amp;rft.date=1999&amp;rft.pages=245%E2%80%93259%2C+at+253&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ala.org%2Fala%2Facrl%2Facrlpubs%2Fcrljournal%2Fbackissues1999b%2Fmay99%2Fdelgadillo.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Primary_source"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> ("[T]he same document can be a primary or a secondary source depending on the particular analysis the historian is doing"); <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFMonagahnHartman2001">Monagahn, E.J.; Hartman, D.K. (2001), "<a href="htt