<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> Handlin (1954)</li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> Marwick, <i>Primary sources; handle with care</i> in Drake and Finnegan (1997)</li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFCipolla1992">Cipolla, Carlo M. (1992), <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=GIqRTlepwmoC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=cipolla&amp;sig=JzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU#PPA27,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=GIqRTlepwmoC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=cipolla&amp;sig=JzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU#PPA27,M1" rel="nofollow">Between Two Cultures:An Introduction to Economic History</a></i>, W.W. Norton &amp; Co., p.&#160;27<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=GIqRTlepwmoC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=cipolla&amp;sig=JzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU#PPA27,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=GIqRTlepwmoC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=cipolla&amp;sig=JzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU#PPA27,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=GIqRTlepwmoC&amp;printsec=frontcover&amp;dq=cipolla&amp;sig=JzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU#PPA27,M1</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Between+Two+Cultures%3AAn+Introduction+to+Economic+History&amp;rft.aulast=Cipolla&amp;rft.aufirst=Carlo+M.&amp;rft.au=Cipolla%2C+Carlo+M.&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.pages=p.%26nbsp%3B27&amp;rft.pub=W.W.+Norton+%26+Co.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DGIqRTlepwmoC%26printsec%3Dfrontcover%26dq%3Dcipolla%26sig%3DJzRVCCjEZperMP0D1yyRewHRMUU%23PPA27%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Primary_source"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRoss2004">Ross, Jeffrey Ian (2004), "Taking Stock of Research Methods and Analysis on Oppositional Political Terrorism", <i>The American Sociologist</i> <b>35</b> (2): 26–37, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF02692395" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1007%2FBF02692395" rel="nofollow">10.1007/BF02692395</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Taking+Stock+of+Research+Methods+and+Analysis+on+Oppositional+Political+Terrorism&amp;rft.jtitle=The+American+Sociologist&amp;rft.aulast=Ross&amp;rft.aufirst=Jeffrey+Ian&amp;rft.au=Ross%2C+Jeffrey+Ian&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=35&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=26%E2%80%9337&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.1007%2FBF02692395&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Primary_source"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> ("The analysis of secondary source information is problematic. The further an investigator is from the primary source, the more distorted the information may be. Again, each new person may put his or her spin on the findings.").</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> David Iredale, <i>Enjoying Archives</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> Sommer and Quinlan (2002)</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> Library of Congress (2007)</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> Everyone has Roots: An Introduction to English Genealogy by Anthony J. Camp, published by Genealogical Pub. Co., 1978</li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/news/stories/104.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/news/stories/104.htm" rel="nofollow">News | Update on document authenticity</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> Handlin et al, Harvard Guide to American History (1954) p 22-25</li>
